4h and seven days a week\n|}\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Europe|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 in the Czech Republic|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in the Czech Republic}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic\n| map1            = COVID-19 outbreak Czechia per capita cases map.svg\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases per million residents by region\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Czech Republic]]\n| first_case      = Unknown\n| arrival_date    = 1 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days\n | month1 = 03\n | day1   = 1\n | year1  = 2020\n | month2 = \n | day2   = \n | year2  = }} ago)\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]] via [[Italy]]\n| recovery_cases  = 71<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| deaths          = 46<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 3,869<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] saw its first three confirmed cases in the [[Czech Republic]] on 1 March 2020. On 12 March, the government declared a [[state of emergency]], for the first time in the country's modern history for the area of the entire country. On 16 March, the country closed its borders, forbade the entry of foreigners and issued a nationwide curfew. While originally planned until 24 March, the measures were later extended until 1 April<ref name=\"apnews\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/breaking/czech-republic-severely-limits-freedom-of-movement-in-order-to-slow-down-coronavirus-spread|title=Czech Republic goes into quarantine to slow down coronavirus spread|website=Radio Prague International|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> and then again until 12 April.<ref name=\"travel ban no 2\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/The Czech Republic medical cases chart}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:80%; float:right; clear:right; margin:0px 0px 0.5em 1em;\"\"\n|+COVID-19 cases in the Czech Republic<ref name=\":0\" />\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Date\n! colspan=\"2\" | Confirmed\n! colspan=\"2\" | Recovered\n! colspan=\"2\" | Deaths\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Active<br / >cases\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Tested<br />(Total)\n|-\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n|-\n! 28 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 193\n|-\n! 29 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 200\n|-\n! 1 March\n| 3 || 3\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 3\n| 211\n|-\n! 2 March\n| 0 || 3\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 3\n| 262\n|-\n! 3 March\n| 2 (67 %)|| 5\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 5\n| 340\n|-\n! 4 March\n| 0 || 5\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 5\n| 407\n|-\n! 5 March\n| 3 (60 %)|| 8\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 8\n| 483\n|-\n! 6 March\n| 11 (137 %)|| 19\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 19\n| 594\n|-\n! 7 March\n| 7 (36 %)|| 26\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 26\n| 787\n|-\n! 8 March\n| 6 (23 %)|| 32\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 32\n| 928\n|-\n! 9 March\n| 6 (19 %)|| 38\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 38\n| 1,193\n|-\n! 10 March\n| 25 (66 %)|| 63\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 63\n| 1,358\n|-\n! 11 March\n| 31 (49 %)|| 94\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 94\n| 1,816\n|-\n! 12 March\n| 22 (23 %)|| 116\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 116\n| 2,353\n|-\n! 13 March\n| 25 (21 %)|| 141\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 161\n| 3,094\n|-\n! 14 March\n| 48 (34 %)|| 189\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 189\n| 4,065\n|-\